{
  "texts": [
    "9.1 Global number of IoT connections Figure 6 illustrates the growth of Internet of Things (IoT) connections worldwide from 2022 to 2024, with projections extending to 2033.",
    "It is anticipated that the global number of IoT devices will nearly double by 2030, reaching over 32.1 billion compared to 15.9 billion in 2023.",
    "By 2033, China is expected to have the highest number of IoT devices, with approximately 8 billion of them being consumer devices.",
    "IoT devices are utilized across various industries and consumer markets, with the consumer segment accounting for around 60% of all IoT or connected devices in 2023.",
    "This proportion is projected to remain consistent over the next decade."
  ]
}